### Record Playwright Traces in C# Test Frameworks (NUnit, MSTest, xUnit)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/trace-viewer.md

This code snippet demonstrates how to integrate Playwright's tracing functionality into C# test frameworks (NUnit, MSTest, xUnit). It outlines the process of starting a trace with options like screenshots, snapshots, and sources in the test setup, and then stopping and saving the trace to a specified path during test teardown. This allows for detailed post-mortem analysis of automation runs.

```csharp
namespace PlaywrightTests;

[Parallelizable(ParallelScope.Self)]
[TestFixture]
public class Tests : PageTest
{
    [SetUp]
    public async Task Setup()
    {
        await Context.Tracing.StartAsync(new()
        {
            Title = TestContext.CurrentContext.Test.ClassName + "." + TestContext.CurrentContext.Test.Name,
            Screenshots = true,
            Snapshots = true,
            Sources = true
        });
    }

    [TearDown]
    public async Task TearDown()
    {
        // This will produce e.g.:
        // bin/Debug/net8.0/playwright-traces/PlaywrightTests.Tests.Test1.zip
        await Context.Tracing.StopAsync(new()
        {
            Path = Path.Combine(
                TestContext.CurrentContext.WorkDirectory,
                "playwright-traces",
                $"{TestContext.CurrentContext.Test.ClassName}.{TestContext.CurrentContext.Test.Name}.zip"
            )
        });
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task TestYourOnlineShop()
    {
        // ..
    }
}
```

